      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FASTOBULLET (2) ran a good race first up in town at Sandown Lakeside, showing early speed and battling on well for third. That looks a fair bit stronger than this run and he was close to a win last preparation having placed in all four to date. He draws ideally and will take a power of catching. JETSETTER JACK (3) just found one better first up at Geelong, beaten half a length. He looks to have come back better this time around and will be charging late. LIBER'S IMPACT (4) is a gelding by Fierce Impact on debut for the Hayes yard who has jumped out well enough to be a factor. IFTIHAR (7) is going quite well with three minor placings to her name so far. She'll push forward and give a sight. SIRVALDANE (5) worked home well last time at Pakenham and has each-way claims off that.",
